      {
        "header": "Narrative and Support",
        "description": "Justification for the request and its impact on the district.",
        "fields": [
          {
            "field_id": "microsoft_forms:01:r3c8a75ec9bdb4a71bc4be4162959661d:8a5fbe4fdba1",
            "label": "Are other Members of Congress supporting this request and/or leading a letter? (If so please specify)",
            "help_text": null,
            "field_type": "text",
            "required": true,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "Yes, Reps. Don Bacon (R-NE) and Judy Chu (D-CA) are leading a supporting letter in the House.",
            "rationale": "References the specific House letter leads mentioned in the congressional support context.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "field_id": "microsoft_forms:01:r901b11f1a0ea49639724f16c7839c707:2130e5d6e564",
            "label": "Please provide a brief explanation justifying the request and how it is a good use of taxpayer funds:\n",
            "help_text": null,
            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": true,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* $3 economic return for every $1 invested in NASA, driving national innovation and industrial competitiveness\n* Maintenance of U.S. leadership in space science to set exploration norms against rapid Chinese expansion\n* Funding for peer-reviewed Decadal Survey priorities to ensure high-impact scientific returns on federal investment\n* Support for a stable aerospace workforce and STEM pipeline essential to the modern technology economy",
            "rationale": "Justification uses strategic advocacy talking points regarding the 3:1 ROI, international competition with China, and the scientific rigor of Decadal Surveys.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "field_id": "microsoft_forms:01:rb1b3498eb8784b11a916c7d2b25c9bd4:055488992bda",
            "label": "How does this request benefit Pennsylvania's 3rd Congressional District?\n\n",
            "help_text": null,
            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": true,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* Direct investment of over $2.9 million in NASA Science obligations (FY23-FY25) within PA-03 institutions\n* Support for Drexel University research on Earth's radiation belts ($786k) and Moon/Mars exploration goals ($498k)\n* Funding for UPenn astrophysics research ($543k) and mission development for the Nancy Grace Roman Space Telescope ($325k)\n* Enhancement of Philadelphia's innovation economy through high-tech research jobs and STEM opportunities at local universities",
            "rationale": "Cites specific NASA spending data for PA-03, including the $2.9M obligation total and active grant awards for Drexel University and the University of Pennsylvania.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "field_id": "microsoft_forms:01:r68378fca7f584dcb9797d018b04fc1e0:70e6acff81b5",
            "label": "Describe the problem or issue to be addressed through this request\n",
            "help_text": null,
            "field_type": "text",
            "required": true,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "Sustained investment is required to maintain U.S. leadership in space science against rising international competition. Without stable funding, the critical STEM workforce at institutions like the University of Pennsylvania and Drexel University faces disruption, risking decades of progress in planetary defense and astronomical discovery.",
            "rationale": "Frames the request around leadership and workforce stability, citing local PA-3 grant recipients to establish district relevance.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "field_id": "microsoft_forms:01:r0e7d5d8c5f0a4b0fb31f9d9262a39755:42077127583e",
            "label": "Please describe the project or program. What will it do and why is it necessary? \n",
            "help_text": null,
            "field_type": "text",
            "required": true,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "The Science Mission Directorate (SMD) conducts decadal-priority research into the Earth, solar system, and universe. This funding supports over $2.9M in recent obligations in PA-03, including Drexel University's research on radiation belts and the University of Pennsylvania's work with the Roman Telescope, ensuring the U.S. remains the global leader in space exploration.",
            "rationale": "Describes SMD's role while explicitly citing the $2,988,696.70 in local spending and specific research activities at Drexel and UPenn mentioned in the context.",
            "confidence": "high"
          }
        ]
